{{Notability|date=May 2010}} {{Infobox ethnic group |group = Japanese people in Pakistan |image = |population = 917 (2013) |popplace = [[Islamabad]], [[Karachi]] |langs = [[Urdu]], [[Pakistani English|English]], [[Japanese language|Japanese]] |related-c = [[Japanese people]], [[Japanese diaspora]] }}
'''Japanese people in Pakistan''' ({{lang-ur|جاپانی}}) form a small expatriate community, as well with people born in [[Pakistan]] with [[Japanese people|Japanese]] ancestry. {{Asof|2013}}, 917 [[Japan]]ese lived in the country, according to the statistics of Japan's Ministry of Foreign Affairs.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.mofa.go.jp/mofaj/area/pakistan/data.html|publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs|publication-place=Tokyo, Japan|date=July 2009|chapter=パキスタン・イスラム共和国基礎データ|title=各国・地域情勢|accessdate=2010-05-28}}</ref> Additionally, statistics from [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Pakistan)|Pakistan's Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] show that roughly 20,000 Japanese tourists entered the country during 2007-08, primarily to visit [[Taxila|Buddhist sites]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thetourist.pk/13-places-explore-pakistan-2018|title=13 places to explore in 2018 - Pakistan - The Tourist|date=2017-12-28|work=The Tourist|access-date=2018-01-06|language=en-US}}</ref>
During the 1980s and 1990s, the population of Japanese living in Karachi alone exceeded over 2,000. Now, the community has shrunk.<ref>[http://www.dhalahore.net/new/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=434:karachi-enclave-for-japanese-investors-at-port-qasim&catid=1:latest-news&Itemid=142 Karachi: Enclave for Japanese investors at Port Qasim]</ref>
==Education== There are [[Nihonjin gakkō|expatriate Japanese school]]s in [[Karachi]] and [[Islamabad]] for the native speakers of Japanese and children of Japanese citizens: [[Islamabad Japanese School]] and [[Karachi Japanese School]]. These schools are accredited by [[Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology (Japan)|Japan's Ministry of Education and Science]] and receive funding from the Japanese government.
