{{Infobox observatory |name = Usuda Star Dome |image = Usuda Star Dome.png |caption = Usuda Star Dome |organization = Saku City Board of Education |code = |abbreviation = |location = [[Saku, Nagano|Saku]], [[Nagano Prefecture|Nagano]] (JPN) |coords = {{Coord|36.1929|138.4293|type:landmark_region:JP|display=inline,title}} |altitude = 935m |weather = |established = {{Start date|1996|11|29}} |closed = |website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> |telescope1_name = 600mm reflector |telescope1_type = F12 Cassegrain |telescope2_name = 200mm refractor |telescope2_type = F10 |telescope3_name = 200mm refractor |telescope3_type = F12 |telescope4_name = |telescope4_type = }}
{{Location map |Japan |label=Usuda Star Dome |lat_deg=36|lat_min=11|lat_sec=34 |lon_deg=138|lon_min=25|lon_sec=45 |position=right |width=235 |flat=right |caption=Location of Usuda Star Dome }}
{{nihongo|'''Usuda Star Dome'''|うすだスタードーム}} is a [[public observatory]] located in [[Saku, Nagano|Saku]], [[Nagano Prefecture|Nagano]], [[Japan]].
Saku is one of the best places for astronomical observation in Japan because of high altitude, high rate of sunny days, and limpid air.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://global.jaxa.jp/projects/sat/alos/topics.html |title=Advanced Land Observing Satellite "DAICHI" (ALOS) - Topics |publisher=[[JAXA]] |date=2002-02-08 |accessdate=2016-09-08 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sakukankou.jp/MT/mtblog/shinsyusaku2016.pdf |title=Shinsyu SAKU 2016 |format=pdf |publisher=Saku City Tourism Association |access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref>
Visitors are allowed to watch stars through the large [[telescope]] from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m.
== History == The observatory was founded by [[Usuda, Nagano|Usuda]]. It was transferred to (new) Saku on April 1, 2005 when Usuda has merged with (old) Saku, [[Mochizuki, Nagano|Mochizuki]], and [[Asashina, Nagano|Asashina]].
== Telescopes == [[File:60cm reflector of USD.png|right|176px|thumb|600 mm reflector]] [[File:20cm refractors of USD.png|right|176px|thumb|200 mm refractors]]
The main telescope of the observatory is 600&nbsp;mm [[Cassegrain reflector]] constructed by Mitaka Kohki. It has the "Wonder Eye" flexible focal extending system which provides "barrier free" star watching.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mitakakohki.co.jp/english/telescope/support-lineup/wonder-eye.html |title=Wonder Eye (Mitaka Kohki Co., Ltd.) |accessdate=2016-08-21 }}</ref>
It is also equipped with two 200&nbsp;mm [[Refracting telescope|refractors]] also constructed by Mitaka Kohki.
